 contribution to the study of media frames during referendums and is key reading for scholars and students interested in journalism, the processes of political communication and the mediation of politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMass mediaxPolitical aspectszScotland. 0aPolitical campaignszScotland. 0aReferendumxPress coveragezScotland. 0aTelevision broadcasting of newszScotland. 4aPolitical Studies 2020. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  aReferendum, frame analysis, media, journalism, news, frame-building, political communication, Scotland.1 aDekavalla, Marina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611990240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526119902423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526119902/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles